			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hi all,<BR>
nice guide here but i have a few comments. first thing i caught was the best place to start. it is a matter of opinion but i beleive Everfrost to be the best place. 1st off they have the large sewing kit right at the zone unlike most other places which these r hard to find. also the best way to increase tailorin technicly up into the 20's or so is spiderling silks! combing two of these makes a thread, 2 of these- a silk bandage, or 3 of the silks whic makes a silk cord used for some even higher level stuff (mainly bags and such i think.) these things can carry u far and if u just hang around the newbie zone ull get tons of em in no time. also there is a bounty of polor bear cubs wandering the same path as the spiderlings that will drup mostly RUINED pelts for ur 1st patchwork though i dont recomend trying till around 30 or so. everything that u make that can be used for other things SAVE! u CAN make muny by just selling threads and bandages but save the threds! infact making bandages is a waste. once u get higher ull be able to make things with these that will make much higher a profit. at my current lvl spider silks r the most valuble thing to me. once u can kill large and giant spiders stok up on these for they make raw silk armor that can be sold to pure casters for 1pp per ac! eventualy u will want a skill of around 41 or up in tailoring AND smithing. this sounds like alot but it saves u muny in the long run. cured silk requires heady kiolas made by brewers and reinforced leather and some other types of armor require steel bonings and studs. also if u start in everfrost u are right by blakburrow and there save up ruined gnoll pelts that cna be combined 4 by 4 into patches then 4 by 4 of those into either another type of patch or the actual gnoll cloak that will eventualy be made. another thing i noticed were the proces this guy had. patchwork is alot more profit than that =) u get the patterns for about 5 silver more or less and can sell a peice of patchwork (depending on size) bak to a merchant for around 5gp! i dont know what player rates r but this is profit quicker. in a couple of tries u can have alrdy made 1pp! alot for low lvls. also personly i like casters when it comes to tailoring b/c melee have to chase down things when their higher like spiderlings while we cast once and BOOM spiderling silks =) well thats bout all i have cept for one more thing: i get ALL my info from www.eqtraders.com. look for their recipie lists and has a list of trivials that u follow till u a grand master =) and just think ive only ben playing for 2 months and have a lvl 14 shammy, lvl 16 mage (the best), and a lvl 8 monk (not the cream of the crop im affraid) and have expansive knoledge of this game. for any flamer or what not that thinks i m some computer nerd: bak down! im a freshman and alot of my time is spent doing homework and what not =( and i DO have friends, a large social life infact! so this proves to people just starting out that alot can b achieved if u just put your mind to it! send me a tell sometime if u c me on the Mithaniel Marr <BR>
Caendar- 16th Mage of the Mithaniel Marr<BR>
&quot;Flamers beware: mages will burn u bak!&quot;
				</font>
